    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-17T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-17T01:00:00-05:00" n="335"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/4068: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-17T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >February 17, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 17—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 17, 11 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d335fn3">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Embassy requests that Commander Jeffs personally inform Americans now at Kuling
                    that Embassy urgently advises them to leave <pb facs="0296" n="290"
                        xml:id="pg_290"/> Kuling if possible and expects them to give this advice
                    their most serious consideration taking account of all factors involved.</p>
                <p>Sent to Davies. Repeated to Hankow, Shanghai, Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
